added.title: Carl SanPedro Part 1
added.description: The Titans fly to Los Angeles but end up in San Pedro, where Berto tells them about the villainous long shoreman, Carl Sanpedro.

added.title: NBTS 2: Chapter Five
added.description: The Titans use to the stems to summon BER, but will it be enough to stop Ultralak?

added.title: An Egg-stremely Bad Idea
added.description: Hoping to 'brighten her day', Izzy and Owen pimp out Gwen's egg chair. But when it ends up in a museum run by angry chickens, they must retrieve it before Gwen destroys the daycare in a temper tantrum of unspeakable darkness.

added.title: Exercising the Demons
added.description: When a severe screen addiction turns the kids into lazy deadbeats, Chef brings in a professional to whip them into shape.

added.title: Soother or Later
added.description: A terrified Duncan, who's afraid of lightning, learns it's even harder to break back into school than it was to break out when he finally escapes and finds himself in a dark alley with Izzy during a thunderstorm.

added.title: Camping is In Tents
added.description: A class camping trip turns into a treasure hunt while Harold is determined to catch Bigfoot and keep everyone safe.

added.title: Mutt Ado About Owen
added.description: After accidentally hypnotizing Owen into being a dog, Harold thinks he must reverse the hypnosis to avoid going to jail.

added.title: The Traveler's Tree
added.description: Guilt-ridden over having lost the Traveler's Tea, Cole embarks on a dangerous quest to the top of a nearby mountain in hopes of finding the legendary Traveler's Tree - a tree which is supposedly guarded by a fearsome beast.

added.title: Krag's Lament
added.description: Cole awakens inside an icy cavern belonging to a legendary beast, and attempts to escape, only to discover a surprising truth.

added.title: Secret of the Wolf
added.description: The Ice Emperor summons an enormous ice Behemoth to attack Lloyd and his faithful wolf companion.

added.title: The Last of the Formlings
added.description: Akita tells the story of the "Choosing" and how she, and her twin brother, Kataru, went into the wilds to discover their animal forms.

added.title: My Enemy, My Friend
added.description: The Ice Emperor's terrible Ice Dragon strikes again, laying waste to the Ice Fisher's village, forcing the ninja to go after Lloyd…

added.title: The Legend of Boggy Ben
added.description: Lion-O has gotten a hold of the last jar of Thundersnaps, the best cookies Thundera had to offer! But a difficult to open cookie jar is gonna send Lion-O and Cheetara chasing down a legend, a Boggy Ben-related legend.

added.title: Prank Call
added.description: Lion-O wants to prove to the ThunderKittens that he's not just some boring old adult, like Tygra, even if it means ignoring his instincts and messing with an obviously evil crystal.

added.title: Best Best Friends
added.description: Master Frown and Brock attend a friendship-themed competition intending to ruin it for everyone else, but soon discover their own friendship in need of repair.

added.title: The Escape Room of Doom
added.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

added.title: Music Videos
added.description: Unikitty hosts a live music video countdown show for the kingdom, presenting the ecstatic audience with the top 4 music videos in the Unikingdom, featuring our favorite characters. Unikitty & Hawkodile team up for a death-metal picnic battle video, Dr Fox sings an 80s synth-pop jam about creating the perfect dance partner with science, Puppycorn sings a ridiculous nonsense song about his perfect day, and Richard unexpectedly closes the show out with the best song in the kingdom, a blistering hair-metal rock ballad with lots of solos and passionate dancing.

added.title: Dunklecorn
added.description: A mysterious relative, Uncle Donklecorn, shows up unexpectedly, claiming to be family. Hawkodile thinks it's just Master Frown and Brock in a donkey costume, trying to ruin things as usual, but Unikitty and Puppycorn are convinced Donklecorn is an old family member. Hawk follows his bodyguard senses and tries to prove that Donklecorn is a fake, until finally the real Master Frown and Brock show up and ruin things, just as he suspected they would. He admits he was wrong about Uncle Donklecorn, but all is forgiven and the friends dance it out together.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers/The Return of Sophie
added.description: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it./The Return of Sophie: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

added.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
added.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik/First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge./First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Blaze of Glory
added.description: Mega Man and Suna must overcome a sibling dispute over what to do on their day off in order to stop Fire Man from overheating the city.

added.title: Nice on Ice
added.description: An "unscheduled" TV appearance not only lands Aki in hot water for missing class, but sets Ice Man on a misguided mission to "unite" (i.e. freeze together) every human and robot couple in the city!

added.title: Hard Times in Silicon City
added.description: Mega Man must stop Blasto Woman from plundering the Museum of the Hard Age and its cache of military grade weaponry.

added.title: Tripping the Light Fantastic
added.description: Mega Man tries to save Dr. Light from a date with "Mari," who's actually Hypno Woman in disguise!

added.title: Running Wild
added.description: Student elections get blown out of proportion (literally) when Air Man lends his support to Aki's rival for class president, Peter Punk.

added.title: The Sleeper Part 1
added.description: Despite finding shelter at MacCadam's, Hot Rod is frustrated with their lack of progress rescuing more bots from the Quintesson Loop.

added.title: The Sleeper Part 2
added.description: Hot Rod desperately tries to free Optimus from the Loop while Perceptor and Dead End investigate why MacCadam's is hidden from Quintesson attention.

added.title: The Citizen Part 1
added.description: Hot Rod, Clobber, Dead End, and Whirl search the long-buried Titan for MacCadam and anything to help them defeat the Quintessons.

added.title: The Citizen Part 2
added.description: Joined by Perceptor, the ragtag team discover the dormant Titan is far more dangerous than they expected.

added.title: The Trial Part 1
added.description: To awaken the Titan Iaconus, Hot Rod plans a daring rescue of the Autobot's only City Speaker.

added.title: The Trial Part 2
added.description: The botched rescue leaves Hot Rod captured by the Quintessons, and the rest of the team to deal with a new, unwelcome bot sprung from The Loop.

added.title: Cuentos de miedo 2
added.description: Es Halloween de nuevo y la banda trata de contar aterradoras historias a un grupo de niños que piden dulces.

added.title: Triquicornio
added.description: Un misterioso pariente, el tío Triquicornio, aparece inesperadamente asegurando ser de la familia. Halcondrilo cree que solo son Master Frown y Brock en un disfraz de burro tratando de arruinar las cosas, pero Unikitty y Perricornio están convencidos de que Triquicornio en un viejo miembro de la familia. Halcondrilo sigue sus instintos de guardaespaldas e intenta probar que Triquicornio es un impostor.

added.title: Videos musicales
added.description: Unikitty conduce un programa de videos musicales, presentando a la eufórica audiencia los cuatro mejores videos musicales del Unireino protagonizados por nuestros personajes favoritos.

added.title: Mascara de Poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: Una Verdad a Medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Huyendo de Casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un Verdadero Lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Pesadilla de Verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y Amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Primera parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.

added.title: Acampar es en tiendas: Segunda parte
added.description: Un viaje de campamento se convierte en una búsqueda del tesoro cuando Harold está decidido a atrapar a Pie Grande y mantener a salvo a todos.

added.title: La Leyenda de Boggy Ben
added.description: León-O se apoderó del último frasco de Thundersnaps, ilas mejores galletas disponibles en Thundera! Pero un frasco de galletas difícil de abrir hace que León-O y Chitara terminen yendo tras la leyenda de Boggy Ben.

added.title: Los ruidos perrunos de Owen
added.description: Después de hipnotizar accidentalmente a Owen y hacerle creer que es un perro, Harold cree que debe revertir la hipnosis para evitar ir a la cárcel.

added.title: Un Dragon en la Guarderia
added.description: Duncan finalmente logra escapar solo para descubrir que ha olvidado su chupete y necesita entrar a la escuela para recuperarlo.

added.title: La Broma
added.description: Cuando intenta demostrarles a los Thundercachorros que no es un adulto aburrido (como Tigro), León-O ignora sus instintos y se mete con un cristal claramente malvado.
